                            <comment id="13975558" author="tdunning" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2014 14:08:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is not that the links have hyphens.  It is that the pages don&apos;t exist any more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a replacement for the BleiJordan link:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://machinelearning.wustl.edu/mlpapers/paper_files/BleiNJ03.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://machinelearning.wustl.edu/mlpapers/paper_files/BleiNJ03.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These other broken links are to our own (former) content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;error Line: 284 &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/creating-vectors-from-text.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/creating-vectors-from-text.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
