The link is broken. Double-check that you have not made any typo, or mistake in copy-pasting. If the link points to a resource that no longer exists, you may want to remove or fix the link.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13975906" author="tuxdna" created="Mon, 21 Apr 2014 20:07:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;If I go to &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/latent-dirichlet-allocation.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/latent-dirichlet-allocation.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I find this url: &lt;a href=&quot;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/-http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~blei/papers/bleingjordan2003.pdf.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://mahout.apache.org/users/clustering/-http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~blei/papers/bleingjordan2003.pdf.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There are two issues here:&lt;br/&gt;
1. The links have hyphen prefixes, which is wrong.&lt;br/&gt;
2. The links may be wrong by themselves as you pointed out.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
